<section>
  <title><literal>EntrySetRelation</literal> relation type</title>
  <para>
    Represents an unordered set of two or more entries.
    Recommended for encoding variants such for example masculine and feminine
    counterparts or spelling variants.
  </para>
  <para>
    Properties:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>label</literal> (non-empty string) eg. "synonyms"
      </para>
      <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
        <listitem>
          <para>Can be constrained and mapped to external authorities by the DMLex Controlled Vocabularies Module.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <para>
    Participants:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>Entry</literal> (two or more, all in the same <literal>LexicographicResource</literal>)
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
</section>
